  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Accurate length determination of root canal is essential in root canal therapy. Radiography
      has been the conventional method for this measurement but recently several in-vitro studies
      have shown that new generations of Electronic Apex locators are as accurate as radiography in
      length determination. It is hypothesized that the latest generation of Electronic Apex
      locator can produce acceptable results as radiography when used for length determination.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
